This article is an executive order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. It establishes safeguards for signals intelligence activities conducted by the United States. The purpose of collecting signals intelligence is to provide timely and accurate information to protect the national security interests of the United States and its allies. The order emphasizes the importance of treating all individuals with dignity and respect and recognizes their privacy interests. Signals intelligence activities must be authorized by statute or presidential directive and conducted with appropriate safeguards to protect privacy and civil liberties. The order sets out the objectives for signals intelligence collection, including understanding foreign government activities, protecting against terrorism and cyber threats, and safeguarding against weapons of mass destruction. It also establishes a redress mechanism for individuals to submit complaints about signals intelligence activities and seek appropriate remediation. The order includes definitions and provisions for implementation, compliance, and oversight.